<HEADLINE>
<P>
HAWTHORNE PARKS FOUNDATION HONORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Recognition for outstanding community service has been received by the 
Hawthorne Parks and Recreation Foundation. The nonprofit organization was 
chosen for the award by the Los Angeles Basin Parks and Recreation 
commissioners and board members. 
</P>
<P>
The foundation was honored for its donations of funds for materials and 
equipment for recreation. Among achievements recognized by the awards selection 
committee are: production of a quarterly program listing Hawthorne Parks and 
Recreation schedules and events; purchase of games and equipment for the Teen 
Center; establishment of the Richard F. Huhn Fund to raise funds for a new, 
multipurpose lodge at the Hawthorne Youth Camp in the Big Pines area of Angeles 
National Forest near Wrightwood, and assistance in providing funds to let needy 
children attend the city's summer camp program at Big Pines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
